WEBVTT

00:21.522 --> 00:23.690
<i>♪ Beautiful dreamer ♪</i>

00:25.025 --> 00:27.027
<i>♪ Wake unto me ♪</i>

00:28.654 --> 00:30.656
<i>♪ Starlight and dewdrops ♪</i>

00:31.949 --> 00:33.951
<i>♪ Are waiting for thee ♪</i>

00:35.661 --> 00:38.163
<i>♪ Sounds of the rude world ♪</i>

00:39.623 --> 00:41.124
<i>♪ Heard in the day ♪</i>

00:41.208 --> 00:42.042
Help!

00:42.125 --> 00:42.960
[whimpers]

00:43.544 --> 00:45.379
<i>♪ Lulled by the moonlight ♪</i>

00:46.922 --> 00:49.216
<i>♪ Have all passed away ♪</i>

00:51.093 --> 00:53.595
<i>♪ Beautiful dreamer ♪</i>

00:54.596 --> 00:56.682
<i>♪ Queen of my song ♪</i>

00:58.058 --> 01:00.477
<i>♪ List' while I woo thee ♪</i>

01:01.228 --> 01:03.564
<i>♪ With soft melody ♪</i>

01:05.399 --> 01:07.401
<i>♪ Gone are the cares ♪</i>

01:08.527 --> 01:11.196
<i>♪ Of life's busy throng ♪</i>

01:12.573 --> 01:15.075
<i>♪ Beautiful dreamer ♪</i>

01:15.951 --> 01:18.328
<i>♪ Awake unto me ♪</i>

01:23.500 --> 01:27.379
[construction workers
shouting indistinctly]

01:28.922 --> 01:31.592
[machinery running]

01:31.967 --> 01:33.218
[buzzer sounds]

01:38.265 --> 01:39.099
[door closes]

01:44.187 --> 01:45.856
Ah, are you shitting me?

01:46.732 --> 01:48.817
I told you I need more hours.

01:49.109 --> 01:51.737
You only got me on the schedule
three days this week.

01:51.820 --> 01:53.822
Joelle has five. What the hell, man?

01:53.905 --> 01:55.991
[man] Joelle smiles
when she comes in the door.

01:56.074 --> 01:58.827
Yeah, bet that's not all she does.

01:59.578 --> 02:00.662
[man, quietly] Jeez.

02:00.746 --> 02:01.705
[door opens]

02:29.232 --> 02:33.028
[phone ringing]

02:33.570 --> 02:34.404
Hello?

02:34.488 --> 02:36.490
[woman on phone]<i> Mrs. Gilbert,</i>
<i>pick up your daughter.</i>

02:36.573 --> 02:39.034
<i>-She's suspended till Thursday.</i>
<i>-</i>What do you mean suspended?

02:39.117 --> 02:41.119
<i>There was an incident in the bathroom.</i>

02:41.203 --> 02:43.664
-Did she hurt anybody?
<i>-We'll explain when you come here.</i>

02:54.257 --> 02:55.717
-You take your medicine?
-[girl] No.

02:55.801 --> 02:58.178
I don't like that stuff.
It makes me sleepy.

02:59.137 --> 03:01.264
It also keeps you
from lighting paper towels on fire

03:01.348 --> 03:02.307
in the girls' bathroom.

03:02.391 --> 03:04.017
What the hell were you thinking?

03:04.101 --> 03:05.727
[bell dinging]

03:07.062 --> 03:08.980
We're gonna talk about this later.

03:09.064 --> 03:10.732
There are gonna be consequences.

03:13.568 --> 03:14.611
Not bad.

03:33.839 --> 03:36.049
[man 1 on radio]
<i>...player gets a top salary,</i>

03:36.133 --> 03:38.301
<i>the next player negotiates</i>
<i>for even higher.</i>

03:38.385 --> 03:39.845
[man 2] <i>They have to go</i>
<i>one direction or another.</i>

03:39.928 --> 03:41.346
<i>You can't be half-pregnant.</i>

03:41.430 --> 03:44.683
<i>You've got a salary cap that you enforce,</i>
<i>or you can just go wild.</i>

03:44.766 --> 03:46.768
[man 1] <i>That's true. Well...</i>

03:46.852 --> 03:50.105
[phone line rings]

03:51.356 --> 03:53.066
-[girl on phone] <i>Hey, Mom.</i>
-Hey, Shannan.

03:53.150 --> 03:55.068
<i>-Hey.</i>
-Oh, glad I finally got you.

03:55.152 --> 03:56.903
-[Shannan] <i>Was thinking about you.</i>
-[chuckles]

03:56.987 --> 03:59.614
<i>-How's it going?</i>
-You know, just another day in paradise.

03:59.698 --> 04:01.908
<i>-What do you mean?</i>
-My boss is a total asshole.

04:01.992 --> 04:04.327
-Gave one of my shifts to the new girl.
<i>-What a dick.</i>

04:04.411 --> 04:07.122
-[Mari chuckles] Yeah.
-<i>I can find some cash if you need it.</i>

04:07.205 --> 04:09.624
[Mari] Well,
that's really nice of you to offer.

04:09.708 --> 04:11.126
-I'll pay you back.
<i>-I know</i><i>you will.</i>

04:11.209 --> 04:14.379
You know, just as soon as I get
on the other side of this shit. [laughs]

04:14.463 --> 04:16.089
-Okay.
<i>-It's been a couple weeks.</i>

04:16.173 --> 04:17.883
<i>-Can I come up tomorrow night?</i>
-Yes!

04:17.966 --> 04:20.343
-Yes, you can come home tomorrow!
<i>-Awesome.</i>

04:20.427 --> 04:23.680
-[Mari] Oh, the girls will be so excited.
<i>-Me, too. Can't wait.</i>

04:23.764 --> 04:25.223
We'll see you tomorrow, baby.

04:25.307 --> 04:26.516
<i>-Bye.</i>
-Great.

04:27.225 --> 04:28.059
[phone snaps shut]

04:35.901 --> 04:39.988
[church bell tolling in the distance]

04:44.534 --> 04:46.536
[objects crashing and clattering]

04:55.545 --> 04:58.632
<i>♪ Beautiful dreamer ♪</i>

04:58.715 --> 05:01.384
<i>♪ Wake unto me ♪</i>

05:01.802 --> 05:04.638
<i>♪ Starlight and dewdrops ♪</i>

05:04.721 --> 05:06.932
<i>♪ Are waiting for thee ♪</i>

05:07.015 --> 05:07.849
[door closes]

05:07.933 --> 05:09.351
<i>♪ Sounds of the rude world... ♪</i>

05:09.434 --> 05:10.560
-Hey.
-Hey, Sherre.

05:10.644 --> 05:12.103
Shannan's coming for dinner.

05:12.187 --> 05:13.605
[singing continues]

05:13.688 --> 05:14.856
If you say so.

05:16.358 --> 05:17.275
[sighs]

05:20.153 --> 05:22.531
<i>♪ Beautiful dreamer ♪</i>

05:22.614 --> 05:25.075
<i>♪ Queen of my song ♪</i>

05:25.534 --> 05:28.119
<i>♪ List' while I woo thee... ♪</i>

05:28.912 --> 05:30.413
[Sherre] Mom, did you ask her to come

05:30.497 --> 05:32.457
-or was it her idea?
-[Mari] No one has to ask.

05:32.541 --> 05:34.334
This is still her home.

05:34.417 --> 05:37.045
I'm still her mom
and we're still her family.

05:37.712 --> 05:41.550
I'm thinking maybe we'll watch
that talent show video after dinner.

05:42.592 --> 05:44.761
I think she'd get a kick out of that.

05:45.303 --> 05:46.179
What?

05:47.138 --> 05:48.098
Nothing.

05:49.307 --> 05:51.351
[Mari] Why can't you be happy for once?

05:58.525 --> 06:02.696
[soft harp music playing]

06:10.745 --> 06:12.247
Maybe she had to work.

06:16.042 --> 06:17.711
She worked last night.

06:22.841 --> 06:23.967
[Mari sighs]

06:55.123 --> 06:55.957
[phone beeps]

06:59.586 --> 07:01.963
[voicemail]<i> This is Shannan.</i>
<i>I can't answer my phone now</i>

07:02.047 --> 07:04.257
<i>because I'm doing something way more fun.</i>

07:04.799 --> 07:05.634
[voicemail beeps]

07:06.092 --> 07:06.927
[Sherre] Hey, Diva.

07:07.844 --> 07:11.222
Look, I know you didn't mean it,
but I think Mom's really hurt.

07:11.306 --> 07:13.016
Even though she'll never admit it.

07:13.600 --> 07:14.684
[sighs]

07:15.727 --> 07:18.438
You should call her and apologize.

07:20.732 --> 07:22.734
Also, your boyfriend called.

07:25.028 --> 07:26.154
Anyway...

07:28.156 --> 07:29.616
I miss you, Diva.

07:43.922 --> 07:47.717
[indistinct chatter]

08:04.901 --> 08:09.823
-[food sizzles]
-[video game beeps]

08:10.407 --> 08:12.409
-[Sherre] Sorry about last night.
-[Mari] For what?

08:13.493 --> 08:16.579
Well, I know you were looking forward
to Shannan coming home.

08:16.663 --> 08:17.497
It's fine.

08:17.580 --> 08:20.250
-Gonna get your butt in the shower today?
-Leave me alone.

08:20.333 --> 08:22.961
-Are you sure you're okay?
-For Christ's sakes!

08:23.044 --> 08:25.714
The world's not gonna end
'cause Shannan had a schedule conflict.

08:27.132 --> 08:30.218
[phone rings]

08:31.177 --> 08:32.012
Hello.

08:33.513 --> 08:34.389
Who?

08:39.811 --> 08:40.645
Goddamn it.

08:42.689 --> 08:43.690
Who is this?

08:43.773 --> 08:45.900
[turns on faucet]

08:45.984 --> 08:47.986
Uh, how did you get this number?

08:48.069 --> 08:49.237
[Mari turns off faucet]

08:49.320 --> 08:53.283
Well, I don't know why you're asking me.
She hasn't lived here since she's 12.

08:53.366 --> 08:55.869
So, if she owes you money,
you're barking up the wrong flagpole.

08:55.952 --> 08:56.786
[hangs up the phone]

08:57.287 --> 08:59.247
-[Sherre] Who is it?
-Some doctor.

08:59.330 --> 09:01.249
What time is it? Oh, shit, I'm late.

09:01.332 --> 09:02.959
He wanted to know if I'd seen Shannan.

09:04.753 --> 09:08.590
Shannan's boyfriend called me last night,
asking if I knew where she was.

09:09.007 --> 09:10.633
I thought they were just in a fight.

09:10.717 --> 09:14.137
I've tried her five times, and each time
it's gone straight to voicemail.

09:15.388 --> 09:16.389
Mom.

09:18.558 --> 09:20.101
He's never called me before.

09:23.980 --> 09:26.524
I'm sure it's fine. Give it a day.
[sighs]

09:27.942 --> 09:28.985
She'll call.

09:30.862 --> 09:32.238
What happened to your hand?

09:34.324 --> 09:36.576
-What happened to your hand?
-[Mari] I burned it.

09:44.125 --> 09:47.128
[excavator hums]

09:47.212 --> 09:48.296
[engine stops]

10:04.437 --> 10:08.066
[indistinct chatter]

10:31.172 --> 10:34.717
It's been 48 hours.
When will you start looking?

10:36.261 --> 10:37.262
For my daughter.

10:38.596 --> 10:40.557
Hello? Hello?

10:41.099 --> 10:43.601
-They hung up.
-They're not even looking for her?

10:44.185 --> 10:45.895
They can't find her in the system.

10:45.979 --> 10:47.272
[Sherre] What about that doctor?

10:47.355 --> 10:50.525
-His number should be on the caller ID.
-It came up "unknown."

10:51.818 --> 10:53.444
He said he was in Long Island.

10:53.528 --> 10:55.530
Maybe we should start calling
the hospitals.

10:55.613 --> 10:57.782
There are hundreds of hospitals
on Long Island.

10:58.700 --> 11:00.326
Did something happen to Shannan?

11:31.357 --> 11:32.442
[engine stops]

11:45.663 --> 11:47.457
A doctor on Long Island called me.

11:47.540 --> 11:49.125
[man] I'll put her in the system, ma'am.

11:54.797 --> 11:55.798
[Mari] Come on, girls.

11:57.717 --> 11:59.928
I'm sorry, but unless
she's physically here with you,

12:00.011 --> 12:01.429
I can't give you any information.

12:01.512 --> 12:04.641
[Mari] Nobody knows where she is,
and the police haven't done a thing.

12:04.724 --> 12:08.186
Now, one way or another,
I am leaving with those phone records.

12:08.269 --> 12:11.147
If you're you're not going to help me,
go get me someone who will.

12:15.235 --> 12:17.111
-She has five.
-[Mari] Five what?

12:18.279 --> 12:19.322
Five cellphones.

12:20.823 --> 12:22.909
Mom, why would Shannan need five phones?

12:23.493 --> 12:25.453
Do you know where this boyfriend lives?

12:26.496 --> 12:29.374
[rap music playing softly]

12:30.041 --> 12:32.126
[Mari] Okay, so when did you last see her?

12:32.210 --> 12:33.086
[exhales]

12:33.878 --> 12:36.714
So, she went to work in Long Island
and never came back.

12:37.298 --> 12:39.467
Wanna know more? Ask her driver.

12:39.550 --> 12:41.886
Okay? He was the one
that was supposed to bring her back.

12:41.970 --> 12:43.888
What was Shannan doing in Long Island?

12:43.972 --> 12:45.848
[boy] Selling Girl Scout cookies.
What you think?

12:46.391 --> 12:48.977
[Mari] Why don't you save time
and tell us what you did to her?

12:49.560 --> 12:50.853
I would never hurt her.

12:50.937 --> 12:52.689
Then why'd you hit her
so hard she had to have

12:52.772 --> 12:54.565
a titanium plate grafted into her jaw?

12:55.358 --> 12:57.485
[boy] You don't know shit about me,
little girl.

12:57.568 --> 13:00.363
And you sure as shit
don't know about Shannan.

13:00.863 --> 13:02.991
You take the money
and the gifts that she buys you,

13:03.074 --> 13:05.201
and you don't think to ask
where it all comes from?

13:05.785 --> 13:09.038
And when she comes home,
who do you think she's coming home to?

13:09.122 --> 13:10.164
Hmm?

13:10.248 --> 13:11.624
I was always there for her.

13:12.208 --> 13:13.042
Were you?

13:14.836 --> 13:16.462
Where can I find this driver?

13:28.599 --> 13:29.934
You two wait here.

13:30.018 --> 13:32.186
Mom,
I'm not letting you go in there alone.

13:34.188 --> 13:36.232
Lock the doors.
We'll only be a minute.

13:36.316 --> 13:37.734
I have my phone.

13:39.986 --> 13:40.987
[doors lock]

13:45.950 --> 13:49.704
-[indistinct chatter]
-[muffled music playing]

13:54.542 --> 13:57.045
[hip-hop music playing]

14:01.924 --> 14:03.009
[man laughs]

14:10.391 --> 14:13.353
I'm looking for Shannan Gilbert.
I'm her mother.

14:13.811 --> 14:15.813
You're Michael Pak, right?
Her driver.

14:22.320 --> 14:23.863
[Pak] You need to relax, lady.

14:24.739 --> 14:25.573
Where is she?

14:26.574 --> 14:27.992
We went out to Oak Beach.

14:28.076 --> 14:31.746
She went in to see a guy.
Next thing, she's freaking out, okay?

14:31.829 --> 14:32.997
What happened?

14:33.081 --> 14:34.332
[Pak] I'm just a driver.

14:34.415 --> 14:35.708
I don't go in.

14:35.792 --> 14:38.544
I wait in my car and then
I drive her home. That's all I do.

14:38.628 --> 14:40.254
-That's all you do?
-[Pak] Yeah.

14:40.338 --> 14:42.298
Yeah, well, you didn't take her home.

14:42.882 --> 14:44.884
Your daughter was hysterical that night.

14:44.967 --> 14:46.219
She ran down the road,

14:46.302 --> 14:48.471
banging on the door
of any house with a light on.

14:49.055 --> 14:51.891
She wasn't making any sense,
she was shouting all kinds of gibberish.

14:51.974 --> 14:52.975
I tried to help her.

14:53.851 --> 14:56.104
But she wouldn't let me,
so I said fuck it.

14:56.687 --> 14:57.855
Oh, fuck.

14:58.314 --> 14:59.399
Oak Beach?

14:59.482 --> 15:01.901
Way down Ocean Parkway,
past Jones Beach.

15:01.984 --> 15:04.153
It's a gated community.
Miles from anything.

15:16.165 --> 15:17.917
This is the last contact we had.

15:21.379 --> 15:24.590
If you live in Ellenville
and your daughter lives in Jersey City,

15:25.883 --> 15:28.052
what the hell are you guys doing here
in Suffolk County, hmm?

15:28.136 --> 15:31.389
Well, her phone records are full of calls
from a 631 area code.

15:31.472 --> 15:33.266
Have you filed a Missing Persons report?

15:33.349 --> 15:35.643
Just phoned Jersey City,
they don't have a record of it.

15:35.726 --> 15:38.980
-Mom, I don't feel so good.
-Just a second.

15:39.063 --> 15:40.898
[detective]
Just because she didn't come home,

15:41.482 --> 15:43.985
it doesn't mean
it's a five-alarm fire now.

15:44.068 --> 15:45.194
Right?

15:45.278 --> 15:47.989
Okay. Then why was her last contact
with anyone

15:48.072 --> 15:50.324
a 23-minute phone call to 911?

15:52.743 --> 15:55.955
[911 recording of Shannan panting]

15:56.038 --> 15:57.832
-[911 operator] <i>Hello?</i>
-[Pak] <i>Shannan, get in the car!</i>

15:57.915 --> 15:59.375
<i>Come on, what are you doing?</i>

15:59.459 --> 16:01.085
[Shannan panting]

16:01.169 --> 16:03.838
[911 operator]<i> Miss, I can't help</i>
<i>if you don't tell me where you are.</i>

16:03.921 --> 16:05.047
[Pak] <i>What's wrong?</i>

16:05.131 --> 16:06.424
[Shannan crying]

16:06.507 --> 16:09.552
[911 operator]<i> I'm having a hard time</i>
<i>getting a read on your location.</i>

16:09.635 --> 16:11.637
[Pak] <i>Come on, Shannan!</i>
<i>Come back!</i>

16:11.721 --> 16:13.723
[Shannan shouts] <i>Help me! Help!</i>

16:14.765 --> 16:16.976
[Shannan wailing]

16:17.059 --> 16:17.894
[phone beeps]

16:18.811 --> 16:20.730
-[recording clicks off]
-[detective clears throat]

16:22.064 --> 16:23.107
All right, um...

16:23.983 --> 16:26.068
The report says the unit arrived at 5:40.

16:26.152 --> 16:28.988
Officers interviewed several residents
who said they...

16:29.071 --> 16:31.949
saw your daughter leave on her own
with no sign of, um...

16:33.034 --> 16:34.452
suspicious activity.

16:37.288 --> 16:38.706
This is her jacket.

16:38.789 --> 16:40.917
[detective] Yeah, well,
as far as the 911 call goes,

16:41.000 --> 16:42.919
the residents say that she was on drugs.

16:43.002 --> 16:45.087
-[tapping sound]
-My daughter doesn't do drugs.

16:45.171 --> 16:46.047
[Sarra taps her feet]

16:46.130 --> 16:48.633
[detective] You got a close relationship
with her, Ms. Gilbert?

16:49.342 --> 16:50.259
Excuse me?

16:50.843 --> 16:53.346
[detective] What was she doing
in a gated community,

16:54.347 --> 16:56.933
100 miles away from home
in the middle of the night?

16:57.016 --> 16:58.434
[Sarra continues tapping]

16:58.518 --> 17:01.103
Can I be frank here with you
just for a minute, please?

17:02.522 --> 17:05.149
When girls like this go missing,

17:05.650 --> 17:07.109
it's a high-risk environment.

17:07.985 --> 17:11.197
You know, I mean, maybe she ran away,
maybe she'll turn up.

17:11.280 --> 17:14.742
Hey. Do you think you could stop that
for one second, please, sweetheart?

17:14.825 --> 17:16.035
Just one.

17:16.118 --> 17:17.620
My daughter isn't on drugs.

17:18.412 --> 17:20.581
She didn't run away. She's missing.

17:21.874 --> 17:25.086
Now, I have been hung up on,
dismissed, and ignored,

17:25.169 --> 17:27.505
but one thing I won't be is silenced.

17:27.588 --> 17:28.673
[Sarra tapping her feet]

17:28.756 --> 17:30.716
Now, you say she's not missing. Fine.

17:30.800 --> 17:33.052
That's your position, but here's mine.

17:33.135 --> 17:35.471
She called for help at 4:51,

17:35.555 --> 17:37.139
and you arrived at 5:40.

17:37.223 --> 17:41.185
How in the fuck does it take an hour
to respond to a call like that?

17:41.811 --> 17:45.940
[muffled rock music playing]

17:46.691 --> 17:47.525
[man] Jesus.

17:48.901 --> 17:50.152
Crack a window.

17:59.996 --> 18:02.957
[music continues]

18:05.626 --> 18:08.045
[indistinct police radio chatter]

18:14.427 --> 18:16.429
[dog barks]

18:16.971 --> 18:18.556
[dog whines]

18:18.639 --> 18:21.350
[dog barks]

18:26.480 --> 18:30.151
[news reporter] <i>Ocean Parkway is shut down</i>
<i>between Gilgo Beach and Oak Beach.</i>

18:30.234 --> 18:32.236
<i>Police aren't saying much, </i>
<i>but what we do know</i>

18:32.320 --> 18:33.988
<i>is that a police dog picked up a scent</i>

18:34.071 --> 18:37.366
<i>and a canine officer, knowing there was</i>
<i>a Missing Persons report,</i>

18:37.742 --> 18:38.993
<i>brought in a search team.</i>

18:39.493 --> 18:40.911
<i>We expect to learn more tonight</i>

18:40.995 --> 18:44.999
<i>when Suffolk County Police Commissioner,</i>
<i>Richard Dormer, holds a press conference.</i>

18:45.082 --> 18:47.251
<i>Commissioner Dormer made news</i>
<i>earlier this year</i>

18:47.335 --> 18:49.670
<i>after narrowly surviving</i>
<i>a vote of dismissal</i>

18:49.754 --> 18:50.963
<i>for staffing level issues</i>

18:51.047 --> 18:54.467
<i>that may have contributed to the deaths</i>
<i>of three voters.</i>

18:54.550 --> 18:55.676
-[detective] Hey.
-Hey.

18:57.345 --> 18:58.346
There's four in all.

18:59.555 --> 19:00.514
They're skeletal.

19:01.182 --> 19:02.642
They're wrapped in burlap.

19:03.934 --> 19:06.354
And they're, uh...
They're spaced evenly apart.

19:06.437 --> 19:08.189
There's... one down there,

19:08.814 --> 19:10.399
here, here,

19:11.192 --> 19:12.109
and over there.

19:17.323 --> 19:20.326
[man on phone] <i>If the press starts to say </i>
<i>we got a serial killer on our hands,</i>

19:20.409 --> 19:22.953
<i>this will blow up.</i>
