20:21.887 --> 20:23.889
[woman]<i> Of course. Don't worry about it.</i>

20:24.390 --> 20:26.016
<i>I got you. Good luck.</i>

20:26.100 --> 20:28.644
<i>-</i>Okay, thanks. I owe you.
-[woman] <i>Bye.</i>

20:30.312 --> 20:32.815
-[Sherre] Hey.
-We gotta go back to Suffolk County.

20:33.566 --> 20:34.650
Mom, what's going on?

20:37.069 --> 20:38.070
Mom?

20:38.863 --> 20:41.574
[sighs]
They don't tell you that over the phone.

20:57.506 --> 20:59.633
[detective] When the units rolled up,
she's a ghost.

20:59.717 --> 21:02.970
Residents seemed pretty calm about it.
Everything seemed to be kosher.

21:03.053 --> 21:06.515
They figured that it was
a domestic disturbance

21:06.599 --> 21:07.767
which resolved itself.

21:08.517 --> 21:10.519
-What do you know about Oak Beach?
-I...

21:11.145 --> 21:14.315
I know the guys like to go to parties
out there once in a while.

21:14.398 --> 21:16.233
-Why?
-What kind of parties?

21:16.317 --> 21:19.653
Oh, come on, Richard, you know.
Birthdays, bar mitzvahs,

21:19.737 --> 21:21.822
<i>quinceañeras, </i>come on.
You know, come on.

21:21.906 --> 21:24.825
-You think this is some kind of joke?
-No. I don't.

21:25.826 --> 21:28.954
Look... she's not in my fucking trunk.

21:30.581 --> 21:33.125
Your real problem is that one out there.

21:33.918 --> 21:34.919
She's feisty.

21:40.132 --> 21:41.008
Okay.

21:42.218 --> 21:43.093
Let me handle it.

21:47.431 --> 21:49.975
[detective] Okay, ladies,
come with me, please. This way.

21:50.059 --> 21:51.435
Come on. Let's go.

22:01.946 --> 22:03.322
[Dormer] Mrs. Gilbert.

22:04.573 --> 22:07.284
Thank you for coming so quickly. I'm...

22:07.785 --> 22:09.328
