35:35.967 --> 35:38.887
There's a crazy lady
about to tear through Oak Beach.

35:38.970 --> 35:40.889
[all giggle]

35:40.972 --> 35:42.265
Come quick.

36:08.500 --> 36:09.584
Who lives here?

36:10.543 --> 36:13.213
[sighs] The son of a bitch who hired her.

36:35.485 --> 36:36.861
[knocking on door]

37:12.522 --> 37:13.356
[exhales]

37:19.446 --> 37:21.030
[Shannan panting]

37:21.114 --> 37:22.031
[Sarra] Mom?

37:26.786 --> 37:27.620
Mom.

37:27.704 --> 37:28.621
[police siren blares]

37:43.303 --> 37:44.304
[Mari] Twelve minutes.

37:45.472 --> 37:49.517
Now we both you know you can show up
on time and your secretary's not a retard.

37:50.351 --> 37:53.146
Can we just go back to my office
and talk about this?

37:53.229 --> 37:54.439
[Mari] We'll talk right here.

37:56.316 --> 37:57.233
This is a...

37:57.317 --> 37:59.486
This is a private community.

37:59.569 --> 38:01.613
Well, then why don't you arrest me?

38:01.696 --> 38:03.698
Listen, I came here to do you a favor.

38:03.782 --> 38:05.909
I don't want to see you
hauled away in handcuffs.

38:05.992 --> 38:08.369
Don't you understand
that when the uniforms get here,

38:08.453 --> 38:12.081
-they're gonna cite you for trespassing.
-Okay, let me get this straight.

38:12.165 --> 38:15.168
My daughter calls for help
but it takes you an hour to get here,

38:15.251 --> 38:16.920
but the Stepford Wives call you

38:17.003 --> 38:19.547
and you show up in less time
than it takes to make a sandwich!

38:19.631 --> 38:23.635
Whatever it is that you're looking for,
Mrs. Gilbert, it is not here.

38:24.219 --> 38:27.096
Okay, then why did my 14-year-old
just find her sister's earring

38:27.180 --> 38:29.432
outside the home of the man
that you just set free?

38:30.475 --> 38:33.394
Shannan went screaming through here
at 4:51 in the morning,

38:33.478 --> 38:35.271
and no one helped her.

38:35.355 --> 38:37.482
Where is the outrage? Where's the concern?

38:38.316 --> 38:40.485
Four dead bodies show up
in my neighborhood,

38:40.568 --> 38:43.238
I'd be shouting from the rooftops
to get to the bottom of it.

38:44.239 --> 38:45.323
What are they hiding?

38:47.575 --> 38:49.452
What are you hiding, Mrs. Gilbert?

38:50.495 --> 38:53.331
You never told me
that Shannan grew up in foster care.

38:57.085 --> 38:59.379
You never told me
you nearly got shit-canned

38:59.462 --> 39:01.297
for mismanaging your department.

39:03.758 --> 39:05.176
Keep up the good work, Commissioner.

39:16.062 --> 39:17.313
[Dormer, quietly] Fuck's sake.

39:17.397 --> 39:20.191
[dog barking]

39:23.278 --> 39:26.114
I wrote down every house number
and license plate I saw.

39:26.197 --> 39:29.200
We need to talk to these people
and these people.

39:30.076 --> 39:31.244
They might've seen her.

39:31.327 --> 39:33.496
[Mari] No one's gonna talk
'cause they want us out.

39:34.455 --> 39:38.251
These guys are looking out for each other.
They all have friends in Suffolk PD.

39:38.334 --> 39:41.838
The police said
everybody passed lie detector tests.

39:41.921 --> 39:44.382
[Mari] Yeah, but anybody
can pass a lie detector test

39:44.465 --> 39:47.385
if all they ask you is "What's your name,
and your favorite color?"

39:48.636 --> 39:50.763
It sounds like Shannan's running
from her driver.

39:50.847 --> 39:53.016
You can hear him in the 911 call.

39:53.099 --> 39:54.267
[Kim] That makes no sense.

39:54.934 --> 39:58.479
I don't care how fucked up I am,
my ass is going to that driver

39:58.563 --> 39:59.814
because he's my way out.

39:59.898 --> 40:02.108
He's my safety.
That's what you pay him for.

40:04.861 --> 40:07.280
Well, maybe he was mad she didn't pay him.

40:07.363 --> 40:09.407
Why would she all of a sudden
not pay her driver?

40:13.411 --> 40:15.622
Maybe because she was bringing money home.

40:17.582 --> 40:20.209
Okay, do you don't know
she didn't pay him. You're just guessing.

40:20.293 --> 40:21.711
Well, I'm assuming.

40:21.794 --> 40:25.548
She's probably forced to get stoned,
drunk, high--

40:25.632 --> 40:27.425
-Not forced.
-[Mari] Okay, whatever.

40:27.508 --> 40:29.552
[Kim] I'm just saying, I've lived it.

40:29.636 --> 40:31.763
Well, I'm just saying, you're not Shannan.

40:35.516 --> 40:37.226
Mari, I feel for you...

40:38.394 --> 40:39.854
more than I feel for myself

40:39.938 --> 40:43.691
or any of the other ladies here,
because Shannan's still missing.

40:44.984 --> 40:46.945
And knowing is better than not knowing.

40:49.322 --> 40:51.115
But you don't really think that...

41:02.627 --> 41:05.964
I'm just saying it might be good to accept
that there's another ending to all this.

41:07.340 --> 41:09.884
What's that ending,
if you know so goddamned much?

41:17.141 --> 41:18.142
[soda can pops open]

41:48.006 --> 41:48.923
[sighs]

42:02.937 --> 42:04.772
[phone rings]

42:05.898 --> 42:08.026
[ringing continues]

42:10.278 --> 42:11.112
Hello?

42:12.030 --> 42:13.406
[man] <i>Is this Mari Gilbert?</i>

42:14.115 --> 42:14.949
Yes.

42:15.366 --> 42:16.784
<i>My name's Joe Scalise.</i>

42:16.868 --> 42:20.204
<i>I have some information</i>
<i>you're gonna want to hear.</i>

42:21.080 --> 42:24.250
[rain patters]

43:09.462 --> 43:11.464
[engine starts]

43:14.217 --> 43:16.761
[Joe] I'm a neighbor of Joe Brewer,
the john.

43:17.887 --> 43:21.390
I got your number
from one of those fliers you posted.

43:21.474 --> 43:24.310
Suffolk PD don't return my calls no more.

43:25.686 --> 43:28.689
You're gonna learn
that the good people of Oak Beach,

43:29.982 --> 43:32.068
if they live by one thing, it's this:

43:32.151 --> 43:34.195
be wary of those who would...

43:35.988 --> 43:38.491
who would ruin a very good thing.

43:38.574 --> 43:43.162
You are, madam,
the wayfarer they've been dreading.

43:44.163 --> 43:45.414
[exhales sharply]

43:45.498 --> 43:46.332
[sniffs]

43:52.672 --> 43:54.841
[Sherre]
I didn't know Shannan was a prostitute.

43:55.675 --> 43:58.052
I didn't know she was bringing home money.

44:00.096 --> 44:01.889
She doesn't let anyone help her.

44:03.599 --> 44:06.018
I thought we were doing this together.

44:07.812 --> 44:09.605
So fucking annoying.

44:11.065 --> 44:12.358
Sorry.

44:12.441 --> 44:13.943
We weren't following you.

44:14.026 --> 44:15.111
We kind of were.

44:15.194 --> 44:16.487
[chuckles]

44:18.614 --> 44:19.991
What are you two talking about?

44:20.741 --> 44:22.201
Families.

44:22.743 --> 44:23.953
Yeah.

44:25.079 --> 44:26.956
Tell me something nice about Shannan.

44:29.041 --> 44:31.586
She graduated high school two years early.

44:33.254 --> 44:34.505
She was smart.

44:35.381 --> 44:38.217
And she was the first one
in our family to go to college.

44:40.428 --> 44:42.263
I called her "Diva."

44:42.847 --> 44:44.015
[Sherre laughs]

44:44.098 --> 44:45.975
Because she's such a little diva.

44:48.144 --> 44:50.271
Amber stood 4'11"

44:50.354 --> 44:52.732
and weighed 100 pounds soaking wet.

44:52.815 --> 44:54.317
[everyone laughs]

44:54.817 --> 44:57.486
Her legs looked like
little chicken drumsticks.

45:01.949 --> 45:03.951
I spoke to her the day she went missing.

45:04.035 --> 45:04.869
[sighs]

45:07.079 --> 45:08.039
We were in a fight.

45:13.753 --> 45:14.587
[chuckles wryly]

45:21.093 --> 45:22.428
-[sighs]
-[car trunk closes]

45:29.769 --> 45:30.853
[Joe] You're walking through

45:30.937 --> 45:33.064
what used to be
the killer's dumping ground.

45:33.147 --> 45:35.024
He only moved the bodies to the road

45:35.107 --> 45:39.028
because this whole area is set to be
drained as part of the mosquito project.

45:42.114 --> 45:45.451
That means people poking around,
seeing things they shouldn't.

45:50.373 --> 45:51.207
Here.

45:51.874 --> 45:52.750
Look.

45:54.961 --> 45:56.963
This is where he keeps his supplies.

45:58.172 --> 45:59.257
But... where?

46:01.926 --> 46:04.095
[vehicle approaching]

46:04.178 --> 46:05.346
[Joe whispers] Go, go, go.

46:05.429 --> 46:08.182
-[Mari panting]
-[Joe shushes]

46:08.266 --> 46:10.643
-[Joe whispers] Shit like that happens.
-[whispers] What's up?

46:11.811 --> 46:12.853
Oh, God.

46:12.937 --> 46:14.563
Easy. Just...

46:18.234 --> 46:19.110
[car door closes]

46:19.610 --> 46:20.528
[car door lock beeps]

46:28.577 --> 46:31.080
Joe Brewer didn't kill Shannan.

46:32.373 --> 46:35.251
He may be a sociopath,
but he's not the psychopath.

46:35.334 --> 46:37.628
That honor goes to Peter Hackett.

46:40.172 --> 46:41.424
[whispers] Dr. Hackett?

46:49.098 --> 46:51.434
[Dormer] Look, I know you
and your buddies don't give a shit.

46:51.517 --> 46:54.103
Don't worry. You're not gonna have to
put up with me much longer.

46:54.186 --> 46:56.897
But for the moment, this is my case.
Okay?

46:57.398 --> 46:59.734
-I want a suspect. I want a name.
-Okay.

46:59.817 --> 47:02.403
[Mari] Peter Hackett. Dr. Peter Hackett.

47:02.486 --> 47:03.988
He lives in Oak Beach.

47:04.488 --> 47:06.240
It's nice to see you again, Ms. Gilbert.

47:06.324 --> 47:08.909
I saw spools of burlap in a shed
by his house.

47:08.993 --> 47:12.204
Come on. What are you talking about?
Every clammer, contractor, landscaper

47:12.288 --> 47:14.999
-has got burlap by his house. Come on.
-But a doctor?

47:15.708 --> 47:18.836
I tell you what, why don't you let
the policemen do the police work, honey?

47:18.919 --> 47:20.796
-Why don't you suck my dick?
-Classy.

47:20.880 --> 47:22.048
This is the guy who called me

47:22.131 --> 47:24.633
the morning after she disappeared.
He said that he helped her.

47:26.010 --> 47:27.553
Come on. Aren't you gonna write it down?

47:27.636 --> 47:29.388
Are you fucking kidding me? Hmm?

47:30.806 --> 47:31.891
Write it down.

47:31.974 --> 47:32.808
What?

47:33.225 --> 47:35.603
I said write it down.

47:35.686 --> 47:38.230
[man speaking indistinctly on TV]

47:55.748 --> 47:56.582
[door opens]

47:58.584 --> 47:59.418
[door shuts]

48:01.962 --> 48:04.340
[brushing teeth]

48:10.179 --> 48:12.098
I googled Sarra's medication.

48:12.181 --> 48:14.350
So I know it's a mood stabilizer.

48:18.354 --> 48:20.940
She told me you took her
to a psychiatrist.

48:21.357 --> 48:22.525
Why didn't you tell me?

48:23.651 --> 48:24.902
There's nothing to tell.

48:25.945 --> 48:28.697
It takes six weeks for the medication
to have any effect,

48:28.781 --> 48:29.990
so we'll know more then.

49:18.539 --> 49:21.000
[man] Hello. Can I help you?

49:24.003 --> 49:26.088
[hens clucking]

49:26.172 --> 49:28.883
[man] Peter Hackett's the best neighbor
you can have.

49:28.966 --> 49:32.303
Ever there's a problem,
he's always the first one to call.

49:32.386 --> 49:34.763
Do you remember anything from that night?

49:35.598 --> 49:37.766
Yeah,
that girl was pretty well drugged up.

49:37.850 --> 49:40.102
-What?
-She couldn't hardly stand.

49:40.644 --> 49:42.688
-Excuse me?
-She almost fell down twice

49:42.771 --> 49:45.274
-when I was talking to her.
-Wait, you saw her?

49:45.357 --> 49:47.526
-Why didn't you call the police?
-I did.

49:48.944 --> 49:51.614
-What was she saying?
-It wasn't making sense.

49:52.198 --> 49:54.492
"Help me. Help me.
They're going to kill me."

49:55.075 --> 49:56.994
So I sat her down on the porch,

49:57.077 --> 49:59.371
and I said, "Relax."

49:59.455 --> 50:02.750
I told her that I called the police
and they were on their way.

50:03.542 --> 50:05.878
As soon as I said that, she ran.

50:06.545 --> 50:07.546
Anyhow...

50:08.506 --> 50:10.883
-What?
-...she fell down the stairs and...

50:11.800 --> 50:12.843
she ran that way.

50:15.888 --> 50:18.390
[Mari] Wait,
do those security cameras work?

50:37.743 --> 50:39.954
[Mari] Is this where they keep
the security footage?

50:40.496 --> 50:41.830
Are you from the news?

50:41.914 --> 50:44.542
We, unfortunately, don't have it
from that night.

50:44.625 --> 50:47.878
It gets taped over automatically.
It runs on a loop. I'm sorry.

50:47.962 --> 50:49.630
But the police got a copy, right?

50:50.589 --> 50:52.675
[woman] We found it odd they never asked.

50:55.886 --> 50:57.388
I'm sorry, who are you?

51:00.057 --> 51:01.475
Why didn't you give it to them?

51:01.934 --> 51:03.519
Why don't I get my husband?

51:03.602 --> 51:05.229
He oversees all that.

51:05.312 --> 51:07.314
I just came by to drop off his lunch.

51:08.148 --> 51:11.193
[breathes deeply]

51:28.544 --> 51:31.213
How can I help you? Dr. Peter Hackett.

51:32.339 --> 51:34.758
My wife tells me you're a reporter.

51:35.259 --> 51:36.510
I've lived here for 30 years.

51:36.594 --> 51:38.596
There's not a thing I don't know
about Oak Beach.

51:39.305 --> 51:43.809
We're like a miniature government here,
and I pound the gavel. [laughs]

51:47.688 --> 51:49.982
Barbara, why don't you put on some coffee?

51:50.399 --> 51:51.400
It's on, dear.

51:52.484 --> 51:54.069
Then why don't you refresh it?

51:59.199 --> 52:03.704
I, uh... recognize you from the news.

52:04.455 --> 52:05.581
I'm so sorry.

52:07.249 --> 52:09.043
-What happened?
-[Dr. Hackett laughs]

52:09.668 --> 52:12.796
Well, that's the $64,000 question.

52:13.922 --> 52:15.507
But you called me.

52:17.176 --> 52:18.135
I beg your pardon?

52:21.513 --> 52:23.223
[indistinct chatter on police radio]

52:23.349 --> 52:26.518
[dispatch officer on radio] <i>Unit report</i>
<i>to mile marker 10.46, Ocean Parkway</i>

52:26.602 --> 52:28.437
<i>for possible remains sighting.</i>

52:31.273 --> 52:33.442
[officer] Just arriving.
Going to check it out. Stand by.

52:59.134 --> 53:03.472
We got a 10-54 on Ocean Parkway
near Cedar Beach.

53:06.016 --> 53:06.892
Fuck.

53:12.690 --> 53:13.941
[scanner beeps]

53:21.490 --> 53:24.993
[Mari] Last place Shannan was seen
was in clear view of a video camera,

53:25.077 --> 53:27.413
and Hackett's in charge of the footage!

53:27.496 --> 53:29.498
Okay. I'll look into it.

53:29.581 --> 53:30.749
He erased it.

53:31.750 --> 53:33.377
What? Did you find something?

53:33.460 --> 53:35.129
Mrs. Gilbert,
you really shouldn't be here.

53:35.212 --> 53:37.464
-Can you take her to the road?
-[Mari] What did you find?

53:38.799 --> 53:39.883
Let go of me.

53:40.509 --> 53:41.677
What's in the bag?

53:42.261 --> 53:44.096
[officer]
This one's not like the other four.

53:44.179 --> 53:46.014
Those were in the bramble a mile away.

53:46.557 --> 53:49.476
There's no burlap on this one, either,
or hyoid bones.

53:52.020 --> 53:54.231
[Dormer] Any indication of a jaw plate?

53:54.314 --> 53:55.274
[officer] No, sir.

53:57.735 --> 53:59.194
[Dormer] Right. Let's go.

54:21.759 --> 54:25.763
[news reporter] <i>Two dozen police recruits</i>
<i>expanded the search for bodies today</i>

54:25.846 --> 54:27.431
<i>from the thicket to the beach.</i>

54:27.514 --> 54:30.392
<i>Suffolk County Police also expanded</i>
<i>the total search area.</i>

54:31.143 --> 54:34.855
<i>This platoon of recruits conducted </i>
<i>a grid-pattern search on Cedar Beach.</i>

54:35.355 --> 54:38.901
<i>It's between Gilgo and Oak Beach,</i>
<i>where the previous bodies were found.</i>

54:39.485 --> 54:41.570
<i>Since last year,</i>
<i>the search has been hampered</i>

54:41.653 --> 54:43.822
<i>by the harsh conditions in the thicket.</i>

54:43.906 --> 54:48.076
<i>Hard, wiry brush called Virginia Weepers</i>
<i>and Bittersweet so thick,</i>

54:48.160 --> 54:50.871
<i>you cannot see a person or dog</i>
<i>just ten feet away.</i>

54:58.253 --> 54:59.880
[Mari] Dr. Peter Hackett.

55:03.050 --> 55:03.884
[door closes]

55:05.385 --> 55:06.386
Kim's working again.

55:07.387 --> 55:10.432
"Carolina" is her street name.
She posted this an hour ago.

55:11.517 --> 55:12.851
[Mari] Oh, Kim.

55:12.935 --> 55:14.311
What is she thinking?

55:19.149 --> 55:20.317
[Dr. Hackett] I'm a busy guy.

55:20.776 --> 55:22.861
I make and take a lot of calls.

55:22.945 --> 55:26.323
But how would I call a woman
I don't even know?

55:26.865 --> 55:27.908
I'm a doctor...

55:28.909 --> 55:30.035
not a magician.

55:33.622 --> 55:36.041
[sighs]
She said that...

55:36.750 --> 55:39.711
that you told her
that you helped her daughter.

55:39.795 --> 55:40.671
[Dr. Hackett chuckles]

55:41.213 --> 55:43.048
I hope she doesn't blame herself

55:44.174 --> 55:45.968
for the life her daughter led.

55:46.927 --> 55:48.095
But...

55:49.429 --> 55:51.765
apples don't fall far from the tree.

55:52.266 --> 55:53.600
[laughing] Am I right?

55:53.684 --> 55:54.643
[groans]

55:55.561 --> 55:56.395
[sighs]

55:57.062 --> 56:00.941
So, what do you remember from that night?

56:02.025 --> 56:06.113
I think that's when Barbara and I
were in Florida.

56:07.239 --> 56:09.241
-[Dormer] Oh.
-You ever been marlin fishing?

56:09.992 --> 56:10.993
But you were here.

56:11.743 --> 56:15.998
Because when the daughter's boyfriend
came the next morning to look for her,

56:17.207 --> 56:19.585
didn't you offer to help search for her?

56:21.086 --> 56:23.422
Florida might have been...

56:24.673 --> 56:26.675
-the week before.
-Oh, okay.

56:26.758 --> 56:30.012
That's right.
I saw this kid tooling around,

56:30.095 --> 56:33.599
and he told me his story
and I couldn't turn him away.

56:33.682 --> 56:36.184
That's what we do around here,
we help people.

56:38.145 --> 56:41.773
[scoffs]
With all due respect, Dr. Hackett,

56:42.858 --> 56:45.944
you're living in a gated community
with a sign that says:

56:46.028 --> 56:47.821
"Be nice or leave."

56:49.072 --> 56:52.618
I don't know that that sends
that particular message.

56:52.701 --> 56:55.078
Look... the police came.

56:55.162 --> 56:56.997
They said everything was kosher.

56:57.080 --> 56:57.915
Right.

56:59.666 --> 57:00.500
But...

57:02.127 --> 57:05.130
why didn't you show them
the security footage?

57:05.714 --> 57:06.924
Why didn't they ask for it?

57:08.216 --> 57:10.677
This is not my investigation, <i>kemosabe.</i>

57:11.261 --> 57:12.846
You're the head honcho.

57:14.723 --> 57:16.558
Maybe you ought to teach your cops better.

57:18.560 --> 57:19.686
A girl goes missing

57:20.354 --> 57:21.521
and you have a tape.

57:23.857 --> 57:27.861
[scoffs] Are you telling me
that you didn't at least watch it?

57:30.155 --> 57:32.240
That would be tampering with evidence.

57:33.992 --> 57:35.035
Am I right?

58:07.317 --> 58:09.945
[Joe] Peter Hackett
is a self-important blowhard.

58:10.529 --> 58:13.573
The very fact
that he's not leading the charge in this

58:13.657 --> 58:16.493
is all the evidence you need
to point a finger.

58:17.035 --> 58:18.370
[Mari] Okay, if that's true,

58:18.453 --> 58:21.206
why wasn't Shannan found
with the other girls?

58:21.289 --> 58:23.834
[Joe] 'Cause the attack on her
didn't go as planned.

58:23.917 --> 58:25.168
She'd gone off running.

58:25.627 --> 58:27.754
People had seen her. The police came.

58:27.838 --> 58:29.840
It just became too risky.

58:29.923 --> 58:33.301
He tells people
that he runs a home for wayward girls.

58:33.385 --> 58:36.013
That he rehabs them. That he saves them.

58:36.096 --> 58:38.348
What he really means is he buries them.

58:39.182 --> 58:41.893
He's got an examination table
in his living room.

58:42.728 --> 58:45.022
And his "home for wayward girls"

58:45.105 --> 58:48.525
is really just code for "graveyard."

58:49.109 --> 58:50.027
Then where is Shannan?

58:51.903 --> 58:53.447
In his backyard.

58:54.114 --> 58:55.282
The marsh.

59:08.211 --> 59:10.505
It's the one place they haven't searched.

59:21.099 --> 59:22.601
[knocking on door, door opens]

59:26.855 --> 59:27.898
[detective clears throat]

59:28.440 --> 59:29.816
We found another one.

59:30.400 --> 59:32.486
Pieces, dismembered.

59:32.944 --> 59:35.030
Forensics says it matches
a pair of severed legs

59:35.113 --> 59:36.698
found in a plastic bag in '96.

59:38.867 --> 59:40.744
-'96?
-[detective] Yeah, '96.

59:41.787 --> 59:45.332
[scoffs] Are you telling me
that somebody's been dumping bodies

59:45.415 --> 59:48.376
in Ocean Parkway for 15 fucking years?

59:48.960 --> 59:49.795
Well...

59:50.378 --> 59:51.755
it looks like it.

59:51.838 --> 59:53.715
Hey, what is this?

59:53.799 --> 59:56.510
Shannan Gilbert's medical records?
Come on, seriously?

59:56.593 --> 1:00:00.055
You really think you're gonna find
any answers in these medical records?

1:00:01.181 --> 1:00:04.476
Look, if she was still around,
we would have found her by now.

1:00:05.310 --> 1:00:06.186
I mean, honestly,

1:00:06.269 --> 1:00:09.106
who spends this much time
looking for a missing hooker?

1:00:18.824 --> 1:00:21.326
If you're here to give me some big speech,
save it.

1:00:22.202 --> 1:00:23.787
I already heard it from the others.

1:00:25.997 --> 1:00:27.332
Kim, I know you're strong,

1:00:27.415 --> 1:00:30.627
and you think you can handle
whatever comes your way, but...

1:00:31.670 --> 1:00:33.380
this is just plain stupid.

1:00:35.799 --> 1:00:37.801
Everyone has their destiny.

1:00:38.718 --> 1:00:41.429
Maybe Amber's was Amber's,
and maybe this is mine.

1:00:44.850 --> 1:00:46.476
You don't really believe that.

1:00:49.521 --> 1:00:53.275
You're only doing this because deep down,
you think that's all you're worth,

1:00:53.358 --> 1:00:55.569
-but that's not true.
-[chuckles]

1:00:59.156 --> 1:01:00.448
You tell that to Shannan?

1:01:04.369 --> 1:01:07.622
[Mari sighs deeply]

1:01:10.000 --> 1:01:11.710
I got Amber into this, you know?

1:01:17.674 --> 1:01:18.550
You tried, Mari.

1:01:27.726 --> 1:01:29.728
-Here.
-Thank you.

1:01:29.811 --> 1:01:33.064
Lynn's boyfriend knew a guy.
We're all wearing them to the vigil.

1:01:36.026 --> 1:01:36.860
[door opens]

1:01:38.153 --> 1:01:39.779
-Turn on the TV.
-Why?

1:01:40.906 --> 1:01:42.115
[Lorraine sighs shakily]

1:01:42.199 --> 1:01:44.784
[Dormer on TV]
<i>...there's also no evidence to suggest</i>

1:01:44.868 --> 1:01:47.621
<i>that it's the work of a single killer.</i>

1:01:48.163 --> 1:01:50.248
<i>Although Shannan GIlbert</i>

1:01:50.957 --> 1:01:54.169
<i>coincidentally went missing</i>
<i>at the same time in the same place,</i>

1:01:54.252 --> 1:01:56.213
<i>she doesn't fit the victim profile.</i>

1:01:56.296 --> 1:01:59.007
<i>She was the only one</i>
<i>who didn't come to Oak Beach alone</i>

1:01:59.090 --> 1:02:00.383
<i>because she had a driver.</i>

1:02:00.926 --> 1:02:01.760
[Sarra] Oh, God.

1:02:01.843 --> 1:02:04.137
[Dormer] <i>We will continue</i>
<i>to look for her, but...</i>

1:02:04.221 --> 1:02:06.806
<i>until we find evidence of foul play,</i>

1:02:07.307 --> 1:02:10.185
<i>Miss Gilbert will no longer be considered</i>

1:02:10.268 --> 1:02:12.395
<i>a part of this larger case.</i>

1:02:12.479 --> 1:02:13.438
[reporter]<i> Commissioner...</i>

1:02:13.521 --> 1:02:15.273
-[Dormer] <i>That's all for the moment.</i>
<i>-</i>Fuck!

1:02:20.779 --> 1:02:22.656
Yeah, this is Mari Gilbert...

1:02:24.449 --> 1:02:26.034
[Sherre] Hey, you okay?

1:02:27.619 --> 1:02:31.081
They stopped looking for Shannan.
They're not looking for her anymore.

1:02:32.165 --> 1:02:34.084
-It's okay.
-What are we gonna do?

1:02:34.876 --> 1:02:36.378
-Hey.
-Why did they...

1:02:36.962 --> 1:02:38.088
That's why we're here.

1:02:39.839 --> 1:02:40.674
Okay?

1:02:41.716 --> 1:02:42.717
Yeah, right.

1:02:47.847 --> 1:02:49.683
-[Sarra sobs]
-You're okay.

1:02:49.808 --> 1:02:51.351
[Sarra sobs quietly]

1:03:02.028 --> 1:03:03.280
[Dormer] I'll just be a minute.

1:03:07.617 --> 1:03:08.451
[house door opens]

1:03:10.120 --> 1:03:12.122
How can you say Shannan's not connected?

1:03:12.205 --> 1:03:14.416
She was last seen
three miles from the other girls.

1:03:14.499 --> 1:03:16.751
She was in her 20s, just like them.

1:03:16.835 --> 1:03:18.336
She was small, just like them.

1:03:18.420 --> 1:03:20.922
She was on Craigslist, just like them.

1:03:21.006 --> 1:03:23.675
None of those other girls
would've been found if it wasn't for her.

1:03:23.758 --> 1:03:26.052
It doesn't mean
that we're gonna stop looking for her.

1:03:26.136 --> 1:03:27.929
-[Sherre] Mom! Mom!
-What about Hackett?

1:03:28.013 --> 1:03:29.723
Even if he did call you, it...

1:03:30.432 --> 1:03:31.808
it's not evidence of guilt.

1:03:31.891 --> 1:03:33.393
Lying about it is.

1:03:33.476 --> 1:03:36.062
I understand that you're angry,
Mrs. Gilbert, but...

1:03:36.855 --> 1:03:40.525
a policeman deals in evidence, not anger.

1:03:40.608 --> 1:03:42.902
Ha, ha!
What fortune cookie did you read that in?

1:03:42.986 --> 1:03:44.446
[Sherre] Mom, hurry. They're waiting.

1:03:44.529 --> 1:03:45.989
Give me a minute!

1:03:48.325 --> 1:03:49.159
[Mari sighs]

1:03:54.914 --> 1:03:56.750
[Mari]
You have no idea, you know,

1:03:57.334 --> 1:03:59.878
no clue what worry really is.

1:04:00.462 --> 1:04:03.173
[Dormer]
We have Shannan's medical records.

1:04:04.466 --> 1:04:05.800
Yeah? What do they say?

1:04:10.096 --> 1:04:11.848
I'll tell you what they don't say.

1:04:12.974 --> 1:04:16.144
They don't say how she used to
shove her fingers down her throat

1:04:16.227 --> 1:04:17.979
and puke until her mouth bled.

1:04:18.480 --> 1:04:21.149
They don't say how she ran out
into the snow one night

1:04:21.232 --> 1:04:24.027
with no clothes on
and nearly froze half to death

1:04:24.110 --> 1:04:27.781
while I was out working graveyards
and doubles just to keep the lights on.

1:04:28.573 --> 1:04:32.660
[Dormer] Yeah. Look, Mari, I know
that you gave her away to foster care,

1:04:32.744 --> 1:04:36.081
and I know you think it's your
responsibility to bring her home again.

1:04:36.164 --> 1:04:38.166
But this isn't on you.

1:04:39.793 --> 1:04:41.002
I'm her mother.

1:04:42.462 --> 1:04:43.630
It's all on me.

1:04:47.175 --> 1:04:49.177
[door opens and shuts]

1:04:52.764 --> 1:04:54.766
[Mari sighs deeply]

1:04:57.185 --> 1:04:58.561
You gave her away?

1:04:58.645 --> 1:05:02.357
Oh, for fuck's sake, Sherre,
can we not do this right now?

1:05:03.691 --> 1:05:04.776
You lied to me.

1:05:05.443 --> 1:05:06.903
I didn't lie.

1:05:06.986 --> 1:05:09.823
You told me the state took her.

1:05:13.576 --> 1:05:15.078
What was I supposed to say?

1:05:16.121 --> 1:05:17.580
"Mommy gave your sister away

1:05:17.664 --> 1:05:19.874
because she couldn't get her
the help she needed."

1:05:20.417 --> 1:05:22.460
Do you think I wanted that for Shannan?

1:05:22.544 --> 1:05:25.171
Do you think I didn't try to do
everything in my power

1:05:25.255 --> 1:05:26.881
to get her the help she needed?

1:05:29.259 --> 1:05:30.969
Shannan was bipolar.

1:05:31.052 --> 1:05:32.512
She was a mess.

1:05:33.096 --> 1:05:35.348
I took her to doctors I couldn't afford

1:05:35.432 --> 1:05:37.392
who gave her drugs that she wouldn't take

1:05:37.475 --> 1:05:40.562
that had side-effects
that I couldn't stand to watch.

1:05:42.230 --> 1:05:43.648
I was just a kid.

1:05:47.402 --> 1:05:48.820
What she needed was love.

1:05:50.447 --> 1:05:52.907
It was the only thing she ever wanted
her whole...

1:05:54.033 --> 1:05:55.160
fucking life.

1:05:56.035 --> 1:05:58.288
Okay, but how do you know
what she felt?

1:05:58.371 --> 1:06:00.206
[Sherre] Because I feel it too, Mom.

1:06:02.083 --> 1:06:04.961
Shannan may be gone but I'm still here.

1:06:07.547 --> 1:06:08.965
I'm still here.

1:06:11.968 --> 1:06:13.178
Oh, my God.

1:06:13.261 --> 1:06:15.513
These fucking women,
they've brainwashed you.

1:06:16.389 --> 1:06:18.850
You wanna know why they're so dead set
on this vigil?

1:06:19.684 --> 1:06:20.977
It's their way of denying

1:06:21.060 --> 1:06:23.021
what god-awful mothers
and sisters they were.

1:06:23.104 --> 1:06:25.815
They've convinced you that
we are like them, but we are not, honey.

1:06:25.899 --> 1:06:27.233
We are nothing like them.

1:06:28.693 --> 1:06:29.569
You're right.

1:06:30.278 --> 1:06:31.362
[gulps]

1:06:33.198 --> 1:06:34.824
No, we're not like them at all.

1:06:36.534 --> 1:06:37.410
They're a family.

1:06:38.203 --> 1:06:39.287
[inhales sharply]

1:06:41.122 --> 1:06:42.499
I wish they were my family.

1:06:42.582 --> 1:06:45.210
Okay. Well, maybe your new family
will pay for your college

1:06:45.293 --> 1:06:47.420
because I sure as shit can't afford it.

1:06:50.423 --> 1:06:52.425
Are you gonna give away Sarra next?

1:06:54.344 --> 1:06:55.178
Hmm?

1:07:01.559 --> 1:07:06.397
[vigil members]
<i>♪ Amazing grace ♪</i>

1:07:06.481 --> 1:07:11.486
<i>♪ How sweet the sound ♪</i>

1:07:12.278 --> 1:07:19.118
<i>♪ That saved a wretch like me ♪</i>

1:07:21.496 --> 1:07:26.709
<i>♪ I once was lost ♪</i>

1:07:26.793 --> 1:07:31.839
<i>♪ But now I'm found ♪</i>

1:07:32.507 --> 1:07:35.260
<i>♪ Was blind ♪</i>

1:07:35.343 --> 1:07:41.224
<i>♪ But now I see ♪</i>

1:07:43.101 --> 1:07:48.314
[humming "Amazing Grace"]

1:07:55.071 --> 1:07:56.197
[sniffles]

1:07:56.906 --> 1:08:01.327
[girl humming "Amazing Grace"]

1:08:14.340 --> 1:08:15.174
[sighs]

1:08:15.758 --> 1:08:17.260
[knocking on door]

1:08:30.481 --> 1:08:31.649
[laughs]

1:08:34.235 --> 1:08:35.236
You're leaving now?

1:08:37.196 --> 1:08:38.031
Yeah.

1:08:43.494 --> 1:08:44.329
Goodbye.

1:08:45.872 --> 1:08:46.831
[sniffs]

1:09:02.472 --> 1:09:03.306
[Kim sniffles]

1:09:06.726 --> 1:09:08.186
[sniffs, laughs]

1:09:08.269 --> 1:09:09.854
Take care of your girls, okay?

1:09:12.398 --> 1:09:14.651
You're lucky, you know?

1:09:20.073 --> 1:09:20.907
[sighs]

1:09:25.870 --> 1:09:27.872
[Mari sighs shakily]

1:09:35.713 --> 1:09:38.174
[voicemail]<i> This is Shannan.</i>
<i>I can't answer my phone right now</i>

1:09:38.257 --> 1:09:40.468
<i>because I'm doing something way more fun.</i>

1:09:40.551 --> 1:09:41.386
[voicemail beeps]

1:09:58.653 --> 1:10:01.698
[rain pattering]

1:10:38.109 --> 1:10:39.777
You can be a real asshole, you know that?

1:10:42.321 --> 1:10:44.031
But you're an asshole people listen to.

1:10:45.199 --> 1:10:47.535
And if they don't, you make 'em.

1:10:50.455 --> 1:10:51.789
I don't got what you got.

1:10:55.126 --> 1:10:57.378
Neither does she, or her, or any of us.

1:10:57.920 --> 1:11:00.298
We was never gonna be
Mother of the Year, but...

1:11:03.217 --> 1:11:04.844
given the circumstances...

1:11:07.555 --> 1:11:08.681
you get my vote.

1:11:21.944 --> 1:11:25.656
[Sarra sobbing]

1:12:11.661 --> 1:12:14.747
[young Shannan over TV]
<i>♪ Beautiful dreamer ♪</i>

1:12:14.831 --> 1:12:18.000
<i>♪ Out on the sea ♪</i>

1:12:18.084 --> 1:12:23.422
<i>♪ Mermaids are chanting</i>
<i>The wild Lorelei ♪</i>

1:12:23.840 --> 1:12:26.801
<i>♪ Over the streamlet ♪</i>

1:12:26.884 --> 1:12:29.846
<i>♪ Vapors are born ♪</i>

1:12:29.929 --> 1:12:36.018
<i>♪ Waiting to fade</i>
<i>At the bright coming morn ♪</i>

1:12:36.102 --> 1:12:38.521
<i>♪ Beautiful dreamer ♪</i>

1:12:38.604 --> 1:12:41.566
<i>♪ Beam on my heart... ♪</i>

1:13:30.406 --> 1:13:34.827
[phone ringing]

1:13:34.911 --> 1:13:36.412
-[Mari] Hello?
-[man] <i>Is this Mari?</i>

1:13:37.246 --> 1:13:38.748
-Yes.
<i>-It's Joe Scalise.</i>

1:13:39.540 --> 1:13:40.625
<i>From Oak Beach.</i>

1:13:41.500 --> 1:13:44.045
<i>Dr. Hackett put his house up for sale.</i>

1:13:44.128 --> 1:13:46.380
[sighs]
Well, great. Call Robin Leach.

1:13:47.298 --> 1:13:49.050
[Joe]<i> His car is already packed.</i>

1:13:49.675 --> 1:13:51.052
<i>He's gonna disappear.</i>

1:13:51.969 --> 1:13:55.139
<i>If you ever want to talk to him,</i>
<i>this could be your last chance.</i>

1:14:23.042 --> 1:14:24.377
[Dr. Hackett]
<i>You wanna talk?</i>

1:14:24.919 --> 1:14:26.087
Talk.

1:14:26.545 --> 1:14:29.382
You've already upended my life.

1:14:30.883 --> 1:14:32.969
You're implying I chased after this girl.

1:14:33.052 --> 1:14:35.513
I can't catch up to myself
walking backwards.

1:14:37.264 --> 1:14:41.644
[kettle whistling]

1:14:41.727 --> 1:14:43.646
-Yes, but--
-[Dr. Hackett] When I was young,

1:14:44.271 --> 1:14:47.608
I was... stranded on a skiff...

1:14:49.110 --> 1:14:49.944
in the water...

1:14:50.778 --> 1:14:51.779
in the dark.

1:14:54.573 --> 1:14:55.700
I was all alone

1:14:55.783 --> 1:14:58.744
and scared I was... gonna die.

1:14:59.495 --> 1:15:00.705
Then I saw this boat.

1:15:02.248 --> 1:15:04.542
It was far away, but...

1:15:05.501 --> 1:15:07.003
I sent up a flare,

1:15:08.087 --> 1:15:09.422
and they came to save me.

1:15:11.590 --> 1:15:12.758
The next day,

1:15:13.718 --> 1:15:16.637
I enrolled in emergency medicine.

1:15:17.847 --> 1:15:18.764
[sighs]

1:15:20.558 --> 1:15:23.019
Ever since, my specialty has been...

1:15:24.979 --> 1:15:26.188
saving lives.

1:15:29.108 --> 1:15:31.193
If she's out there, we gotta find her.

1:15:35.906 --> 1:15:37.283
You're the real hero.

1:15:39.201 --> 1:15:41.537
A mother who would go to any lengths

1:15:42.705 --> 1:15:43.748
for her daughter.

1:15:46.917 --> 1:15:49.336
That is true heroism.

1:15:56.218 --> 1:15:57.553
-[door shuts]
-[Dormer] Oh.

1:15:58.554 --> 1:15:59.638
Mrs. Gilbert.

1:16:02.224 --> 1:16:03.559
Nice to see you again.

1:16:04.643 --> 1:16:07.104
[Mari] Don't worry.
I left my staple gun at home.

1:16:07.188 --> 1:16:08.022
[chuckles]

1:16:08.731 --> 1:16:10.107
So how did you get in my office?

1:16:11.150 --> 1:16:12.777
It's not your office anymore.

1:16:13.444 --> 1:16:15.154
True. True.

1:16:16.781 --> 1:16:20.826
Yeah, they're putting me out to pasture,
as they say.

1:16:20.910 --> 1:16:23.329
What do you think
you'll be most remembered for?

1:16:24.330 --> 1:16:25.873
What can I help you with?

1:16:29.335 --> 1:16:30.878
Why haven't you searched the marsh?

1:16:31.754 --> 1:16:34.590
It's the only place in Oak Beach
you haven't searched.

1:16:34.673 --> 1:16:37.927
Because a grown man
can't get through there,

1:16:38.010 --> 1:16:40.554
never mind a 100-pound girl.

1:16:40.638 --> 1:16:43.599
Yeah, but it borders Anchor Way
where Shannan was last seen,

1:16:43.682 --> 1:16:46.018
and Larboard Court
where Peter Hackett lives.

1:16:46.102 --> 1:16:48.771
Ah, so this is about Hackett.

1:16:49.396 --> 1:16:51.565
We've already cleared him.

1:16:51.649 --> 1:16:53.943
What... You gotta talk to Joe Scalise.

1:16:54.026 --> 1:16:57.863
Joe Scalise
is a paranoid conspiracy freak.

1:16:57.947 --> 1:16:59.532
He and Hackett hate each other.

1:16:59.615 --> 1:17:01.826
Some dispute they had years ago over land.

1:17:02.409 --> 1:17:03.661
He wants to bury Hackett.

1:17:03.744 --> 1:17:05.079
Maybe he's giving you the shovel.

1:17:05.996 --> 1:17:07.540
What about her jacket?

1:17:08.165 --> 1:17:11.961
If Hackett had contact with Shannan,
her jacket would prove it.

1:17:12.044 --> 1:17:14.922
It would have skin cells
or fibers on it or something.

1:17:17.967 --> 1:17:19.301
We don't have the jacket.

1:17:20.553 --> 1:17:23.055
When they first picked it up,
Shannan wasn't officially missing

1:17:23.139 --> 1:17:24.849
and it got lost.

1:17:27.726 --> 1:17:31.188
What is this, some kind of cover-up
or just incompetence?

1:17:31.772 --> 1:17:33.983
Search the marsh or I'm going on the news.

1:17:39.029 --> 1:17:40.197
[door bangs shut]

1:17:40.281 --> 1:17:44.827
["Juicy Fruit (Disco Freak)" playing]

1:18:21.780 --> 1:18:24.575
[news reporter] <i>A year ago,</i>
<i>the police first discovered the remains</i>

1:18:24.658 --> 1:18:28.621
<i>of three bodies dumped along</i>
<i>the side of the road off Ocean Park--</i>

1:18:29.121 --> 1:18:33.751
[sirens wailing]

1:18:52.561 --> 1:18:54.438
-What's happening?
-They're draining the marsh,

1:18:55.105 --> 1:18:56.565
looking for that hooker.

1:18:57.149 --> 1:18:58.567
-[sighs]
-[Lorraine] Mari!

1:18:59.443 --> 1:19:00.277
Lorraine.

1:19:02.696 --> 1:19:05.950
-What are you doing here?
-I came for the anniversary vigil.

1:19:06.408 --> 1:19:07.952
The others are on their way.

1:19:08.035 --> 1:19:09.119
Hey, don't worry.

1:19:09.703 --> 1:19:12.373
We're not gonna let you
go through this alone. All right?

1:19:14.083 --> 1:19:16.085
[news reporter]
<i>Heavy equipment, including a backhoe,</i>

1:19:16.168 --> 1:19:18.754
<i>were brought in to dig through</i>
<i>the thick brush and marsh.</i>

1:19:18.837 --> 1:19:21.131
<i>The commissioner says</i>
<i>the area was too tough</i>

1:19:21.215 --> 1:19:23.300
<i>for the searchers to get through on foot.</i>

1:19:24.468 --> 1:19:27.721
<i>Here in Oak Beach,</i>
<i>missing sex worker, Shannan Gilbert,</i>

1:19:27.805 --> 1:19:30.641
<i>was last seen alive</i>
<i>leaving a client's house.</i>

1:19:31.016 --> 1:19:33.227
[male reporter] <i>During the search</i>
<i>for Shannan Gilbert last year,</i>

1:19:33.310 --> 1:19:35.020
<i>four other bodies were discovered.</i>

1:19:35.104 --> 1:19:39.358
<i>There are now ten sets of remains,</i>
<i>half of whom are still unidentified.</i>

1:19:39.441 --> 1:19:41.902
[female reporter] <i>According to the police,</i>
<i>Shannan Gilbert's disappearance</i>

1:19:41.986 --> 1:19:43.362
<i>is unrelated to those.</i>

